<item>
            <title>[LU-19520] FLR-EC: Don&apos;t read parity components on old clients</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19520</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We need to make sure that older clients do not try to read the parity components. This can probably be handled by setting the layout pattern of the parity components to &lt;tt&gt;LOV_PATTERN_PARITY&lt;/tt&gt;, but this needs to be tested.  It may be desirable to exclude the &lt;tt&gt;LOV_PATTERN_PARITY&lt;/tt&gt; components from the layout that is sent to older clients, since 2.15.x does not (yet) have patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/51060&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/51060&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16837&quot; title=&quot;interop: client skip unknown component mirror&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16837&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16837&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: handle unknown layout component&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) to handle FLR-EC layouts properly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="93181">LU-19520</key>
            <summary>FLR-EC: Don&apos;t read parity components on old clients</summary>
